  m_Name: Trifolium
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::PlantInfoData
  plantName: Trifolium
  description: Trifolium is a genus of roughly 255 species of herbaceous flowering
    plants in the bean family (Fabaceae), commonly known as clover or trefoil. Derived
    from Latin for "three-leafed," these low-growing, nitrogen-fixing perennials
    or annuals are characterized by trifoliate leaves, small white/pink/yellow flower
    heads, and widespread use as forage, cover crops, and lawns.
